l,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Place a 10-inch cast iron skillet on middle rack in oven and preheat\n   to 425°F (220°C). In a medium bowl, whisk together cornmeal, flour,\n   sugar, baking powder, salt, and baking soda. In a separate medium\n   bowl, whisk together sour cream, buttermilk, eggs, 3 tablespoons\n   melted butter, and canola oil. Pour wet ingredients into bowl with\n   dry ingredients and whisk until completely combined. Stir in cheese\n   and jalapeños.\n"]],["item",{"bullet":"2. ","checkbox":null,"counter":null,"pre-blank":0,"tag":null,"begin":1227,"post-affiliated":1227,"contents-begin":1230,"contents-end":1708,"end":1708,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"item","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":[[788,0,"1. ",null,null,null,1227],[1227,0,"2. ",null,null,null,1708]],"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":1230,"post-affiliated":1230,"contents-begin":1230,"contents-end":1708,"end":1708,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Using pot holders, carefully remove hot pan from oven. Place 1\n   tablespoon butter in skillet and swirl to completely melt and coat\n   inside of pan. Pour in cornbread batter and place in oven. Bake until\n   skewer inserted into middle of cornbread comes out clean, about 20\n   minutes. Let bread cool in pan for 5 minutes, then carefully turn out\n   to wire rack and let cool an additional 10 minutes. Serve\n   immediately. Reheat any leftover cornbread before serving again.\n"]]]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":0,"raw-value":"Make Ahead And Storage","title":["Make Ahead And Storage"],"level":1,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"comment